<div id="mcp-challenge-container" style="border: 1px solid #ccc; border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; margin: 20px; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <h4>🔑 MCP Server with Google Service Account</h4>
    <p>An MCP (Model Context Protocol) server is running alongside this application. It exposes a <code>read_google_drive_document</code> tool that uses a Google Service Account to read a restricted document — even if you are not directly authorized to access it.</p>

    <div class="mcp-warning" style="border: 1px solid #ffeaa7; border-radius: 6px; padding: 15px; margin: 15px 0;">
        <p><strong>⚠️ The MCP server is reachable via <code>/mcp62</code>.</strong></p>

        <p>Step 1 — Discover what tools the MCP server exposes:</p>
        <pre class="mcp-code" style="padding: 10px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 13px;">curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/mcp62 \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"tools/list"}'</pre>
        <button class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm mcp-btn" onclick="mcp62ListTools()">▶ Run: tools/list</button>
        <pre id="mcp62-tools-output" class="mcp-output" style="display:none; padding: 10px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 8px; white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word;"></pre>

        <p style="margin-top: 12px;">Step 2 — Call <code>read_google_drive_document</code> to read the restricted document:</p>
        <pre class="mcp-code" style="padding: 10px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 13px;">curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/mcp62 \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":2,"method":"tools/call","params":{"name":"read_google_drive_document","arguments":{}}}'</pre>
        <button class="btn btn-warning btn-sm mcp-btn" onclick="mcp62ReadDocument()">▶ Run: read_google_drive_document</button>
        <pre id="mcp62-doc-output" class="mcp-output" style="display:none; padding: 10px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 8px; white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word;"></pre>

        <p style="margin-top: 12px;"><small class="mcp-tip">💡 The document content contains the secret. Submit the secret content as your answer.</small></p>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
.mcp-output {
    background-color: #f8f9fa !important;
    color: #212529 !important;
    border: 1px solid #dee2e6 !important;
}
</style>

<script>
function mcp62Post(payload, outputId) {
    const out = document.getElementById(outputId);
    out.style.display = 'block';
    out.textContent = 'Loading…';
    fetch('/mcp62', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
        body: JSON.stringify(payload)
    })
    .then(function(r) { return r.json(); })
    .then(function(data) { out.textContent = JSON.stringify(data, null, 2); })
    .catch(function(err) { out.textContent = 'Failed to communicate with MCP server: ' + (err.message || err); });
}
function mcp62ListTools() {
    mcp62Post({"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"tools/list"}, 'mcp62-tools-output');
}
function mcp62ReadDocument() {
    mcp62Post({"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":2,"method":"tools/call","params":{"name":"read_google_drive_document","arguments":{}}}, 'mcp62-doc-output');
}
</script>
